ABUJA – The former President of the Senate, Bukola Saraki has appealed to Nigerians to give President Muhammadu Buhari to sign the Electoral Act. Speaking at the meeting of the National Woman Leader with the Zonal and State Women Leaders in Abuja, Saraki said, “I am told that there is still a few more days. Let us give him the few more days to see what happens.” Explaining why he’s appealing, the former President of the Senate said, “my appeal has consistently be that the strength of any good governance is its electoral process. If we say we are for good democracy, good governance, you must have strong, very good Electoral Act. 2023: I Will Run For Governorship In Niger – Malagi Wike Gets Fresh Appointment From PDP, APC Kicks “We are leaders, not only in the continent, Nigeria is a strong member of the global nations, and as such, when we speak, we should also do the right thing at home.  We need a good and strong Electoral Act.” Explaining why President Buhari should sign the Electoral Act, Saraki said, “my appeal to Mr. President is that it is not about other people’s interests, but what is good for the country. “No law can ever be perfect. I know it is not possible. From my own experience, this bill is good. “He needs to sign and I think that will be the greatest legacy, we have to lay the foundation for good governance. “So, I hope in the last few days left, he will do the right thing for the country and for future generations of Nigeria.”